I seriously doubt it.

 

Canadarm for example, isn't up to date.
And are you using blizzy's original toolbar (1.2) or Toolbar Continued by linuxgurugamer (1.3)?
Scatterer is another one that jumps out that hasn't been updated for 1.3

 

I would do a clean install and add the mods you want piecemeal AFTER checking the required KSP version.
Dont' forget to delete ModuleManager's cache files (delete everything with ModuleManager in the filename except the .dll)


And PLEASE get your logs out off your post and add them as a Dropbox link or something. This is murdering my browser!

Those embedded files are murder on mobile devices.

Either remove them, or forgo any help from people on mobile.

To @schneemannski and anyone else who may be reading this:

Please do not paste huge text files into forum posts.  I know you don't mean any harm, but it wrecks people's browsers.  Even on a desktop, with a high-speed wired connection and plenty of RAM, it causes awkward, irritating lag in browsers; and for anyone on a mobile device-- even if they're on Wi-Fi and not using precious mobile bandwidth-- it can make the browser lock up entirely.

Sharing log files is a great way to help people diagnose your problem, and you should absolutely do it.  But don't paste them directly into the forum.  Instead, put your log on some third-party sharing site-- there are lots of them out there on the internet-- and link to it from your forum post.

I've edited the OP and one follow-up post here to remove the huge log files.  If you haven't solved your problem yet, feel free to re-post your log files somewhere-- i.e. elsewhere, not in the forum-- and link it here, and I'm sure plenty of folks will be happy to help. 

Thank you for your understanding..
